      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         <p>The Central New York Coalition for Adult and Continuing Education (CNY-CACE) started out as the Metropolitan Syracuse Committee on Adult and Continuing Education in the early 1960s.
         They were an adult education organization with connections and programming across Metropolitan Syracuse.
         The purpose of the organization was to facilitate the professional development and networking of members; promote community awareness of adult and continuing education programs and opportunities; provide various services to the community through workshops, information sessions, and written materials; foster a setting in which adult and continuing education professionals can develop and enhance their leadership skills;
         and formally recognize the achievements of adult learners. </p>
      </bioghist>

      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Central New York Coalition for Adult and Continuing Education (CNY-CACE) Records</emph> contains administration files, conference materials, presidents’ files, and printed materials</p>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Administration files</emph>, 1989-1999 encompass many content formats and materials related to the general administrative functions and aspects of the organization including budget materials, bylaws correspondence, minutes, notes, and reports.</p>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Conference Materials, 1990-1999</emph> are materials related to CNY-CACE conferences and other conferences. For conference materials by CNY-CACE include planning materials, surveys, workshop materials, and conference ephemera. The materials by others include printed material from conferences, conference handouts, conference informational materials, and more.</p>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Presidents’ files, 1989-1999</emph> is a series containing materials corresponding to presidential leadership throughout the organizations’ history. Materials in this series include business cards, correspondence, faxes, notes, and other materials.</p>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Printed Materials, 1990-1999</emph> include brochures, fliers, and newsletters related and created by CNY-CACE and by others.</p>
      </scopecontent>

      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Collection Arrangement</head>
         <p>The confererence materials are arranged chronologically and the rest of the collection is arranged alphabetically.</p>
      </arrangement>

      <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1">
         <head>Related Material</head>
         <p>SCRC holds numerous collections related to adult and continuing education. The adult education holdings are collectively known as the <extref href="https://library.syracuse.edu/special-collections-research-center/collections/collection-areas/charters-library/">Alexander N. Charters Library of Resources for Educators of Adults.</extref> Please refer to <extref href="https://library.syracuse.edu/digital/guides/ead/subj_list_from_db.htm">the SCRC Subject Index</extref> for a complete listing of all adult education collections. In particular, see the <archref href="caeo.htm">Coalition of Adult Education Organizations (CAEO) Records</archref> and <archref href="cepamp.htm">Continuing Education Pamphlet Collection.</archref></p>
      </relatedmaterial>

